\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {15}{\ignorespaces A non-LAS baseline: clean-label recovery (MCC) on the per-argument acceptance task, over the same pool and grouped five-fold CV. A feature-based decision tree and the strongest feature learner (random forest / depth-12 tree) plateau well below the LAS route's exact recovery (Sections~\ref {sec:mech}--\ref {sec:exp1}), and closest only on complete/grounded (a single-extension, near-functional target). A per-argument classifier cannot represent the extension \emph  {set} that LAS learns.}}{45}{figure.15}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:baseline_comparison}{{15}{45}{A non-LAS baseline: clean-label recovery (MCC) on the per-argument acceptance task, over the same pool and grouped five-fold CV. A feature-based decision tree and the strongest feature learner (random forest / depth-12 tree) plateau well below the LAS route's exact recovery (Sections~\ref {sec:mech}--\ref {sec:exp1}), and closest only on complete/grounded (a single-extension, near-functional target). A per-argument classifier cannot represent the extension \emph {set} that LAS learns}{figure.15}{}}
\def\@LN@column{1}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {16}{\ignorespaces Two decision trees learned agnostically from structure (clean labels, fold~1), shown after collapsing constant subtrees. \textbf  {(a)}~Grounded: three legible rules approximating grounded acceptance (reachability from the unattacked core, minus direct undefended attack), the target feature learners fit best. \textbf  {(b)}~Credulous-stable: one clean rule, then a tangle of $\sim $20 splits whose leaves mix \textsf  {in}/\textsf  {out} with no coherent rule --- credulous stable acceptance is a global property of the extension \emph  {set} that local features cannot capture. Grounded is functional (one extension), so a local heuristic gets close; stable is multi-extension, so it does not.}}{46}{figure.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:learned_trees}{{16}{46}{Two decision trees learned agnostically from structure (clean labels, fold~1), shown after collapsing constant subtrees. \textbf {(a)}~Grounded: three legible rules approximating grounded acceptance (reachability from the unattacked core, minus direct undefended attack), the target feature learners fit best. \textbf {(b)}~Credulous-stable: one clean rule, then a tangle of $\sim $20 splits whose leaves mix \pred {in}/\pred {out} with no coherent rule --- credulous stable acceptance is a global property of the extension \emph {set} that local features cannot capture. Grounded is functional (one extension), so a local heuristic gets close; stable is multi-extension, so it does not}{figure.16}{}}
